In the above equations, A is the plate surface area, ␥wl and ␥wv are the wall-liquid and wall-vapor interfacial tensions ͑⌬␥ ϵ ␥wl − ␥wv͒, P is the bulk pressure, and P* is the equi-
librium vapor pressure at the given temperature. It follows
from Eq. ͑2͒ that dth decreases with increasing P, as manifest in Fig. 2. For an incompressible liquid, P − P* = ␳l͑␮l − ␮v͒, and, therefore ͓21,35͔,

